<!-- OVERVIEW -->
<section class="overview-section" id="overview">
<div class="section-inner">
<div class="section-eyebrow">The philosophy</div>
<h2>Structured, but not bureaucratic.</h2>
<div class="overview-grid">
<div class="overview-left">
<p>Rather than relying only on static documentation and closed decision-making, engage uses a structured process that combines methodology with practical dialogue and informed participation.</p>
<p>At a high level, the process moves through five stages — from executive alignment through to handover and internal ownership. Each stage is designed to increase clarity, build confidence, and reduce the friction often associated with traditional grading exercises.</p>
</div>
<div>
<ul class="principle-list">
<li class="principle-item"><div class="p-dot"></div><div><strong>Committee-based by design</strong><span>Roles are evaluated through informed discussion, not closed-door specialist decisions.</span></div></li>
<li class="principle-item"><div class="p-dot"></div><div><strong>Transparency throughout</strong><span>The methodology, the judgement, and the reasoning can all be explained at every stage.</span></div></li>
<li class="principle-item"><div class="p-dot"></div><div><strong>Built for internal ownership</strong><span>The goal is not permanent dependency. The goal is long-term internal capability.</span></div></li>
<li class="principle-item"><div class="p-dot"></div><div><strong>Practically useful output</strong><span>The result is not just academically correct. It is designed to be used with confidence.</span></div></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>
